article.headline: N. Carolina A&amp,T 68, Winston-Salem 61
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Tavarus Alston scored 15 points and North Carolina A&T defeated Winston-Salem 68-61 on Saturday. Thomas Coleman and Ed Jones added 12 points each for the Aggies (14-13). North Carolina A&T shot 41.3 percent from the field for its sixth straight victory. The Rams (7-18) connected on 42.6 percent of their shots (26 of 61), while making 24 percent from 3-point range (6-for-25). Brian Fisher, who has led the Rams in scoring over the last four games, finished with 25 points. Fisher went 5-for-13 from behind the 3-point arc and added four assists. Jemarcus McClinton chipped in 14 points for Winston-Salem. North Carolina A&T defeated the Rams for the second time this season. The first was a 73-60 win in Winston-Salem on Jan. 24.
